      "translation": "My father's name is Thomas"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "'Mutter' is a feminine noun, so 'meine' takes an -e ending. Unlike English, German changes the possessive form based on the gender of the noun.",
      "sentence": "Meine Mutter arbeitet viel",
      "translation": "My mother works a lot"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "'Bruder' (brother) is masculine, so we use 'mein'. Word order here is subject-verb-object, just like in English.",
