      "explanation": "'Eltern' (parents) is always plural in German, so it uses the plural possessive 'meine' and no singular form is common. There's no direct singular like English 'parent' in everyday use.",
      "sentence": "Meine Eltern wohnen hier",
      "translation": "My parents live here"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "'Liebe' means 'love' and here it functions as a verb ('I love'). The object 'meine Familie' takes the accusative, but 'Familie' looks the same as in the nominative.",
      "sentence": "Ich liebe meine Familie",
      "translation": "I love my family"
    }
  ]
}

{
