    }
  ]
}

{
  "sentences": [
    {
      "explanation": "빨간색 (ppalgansaek) means 'red' and 이에요 (ieyo) is the polite 'is/are' ending. Unlike English, Korean puts the 'to be' verb at the end of the sentence.",
