    {
      "explanation": "초록색 (choroksaek) means 'green.' The verb 좋아해요 (joahaeyo) means 'like,' and it goes at the very end — Korean word order is subject-object-verb, unlike English subject-verb-object.",
      "sentence": "제 친구는 초록색을 좋아해요",
